SAVE this RECIPE ✨
Here is my No FAIL CARMEL RECIPE- for Carmel apples- 
love this because it makes enough to dip 10-12 medium apples! 
Make sure you cook to the hard ball stage 
Then it will be easy to 
Dip the Carmel apples in 
WHITE chocolate immediately after the Carmel…
can also dip in cinnamon sugar 
And Oreos 
Or whatever you want! 
Fun for a get together or party!

Recipe BELOW

Carmel apples are a fall tradition

Friends 
I’m just about ready to share a few things I’ve been working on

Carmel Recipe
1 cup brown sugar 
1 cup corn syrup
1 cube and 1/2 of butter 
Bring to a boil 
And then add 
One can of 
Sweetened condensed milk

Stirring constantly on medium heat. 
And then you bring to a hardball stage 

We don’t use a thermometer 
We check it within a few minutes of adding the sweetened condensed milk 

to check 
**A cup of cold water 
Drop some Carmel in and pour out water and see how quick it goes into a ball 
You want a medium firm ball 
Keep checking 
Till it gets to this stage 

ENJOY!!

Save!!! Cook Christmas morning👏🏻✨ Super easy…prep time is about 10min right when you go to bed…
They will rise in the night and be ready to pop in the oven for your Christmas morning breakfast!! 

This has been one of our longest favorite family traditions💕🤩✨
Please Tag me if you try them 

✨Recipe✨
pull aparts

14-16 frozen rolls 
1 3/4 cube of butter 
1 package of cook and serve butterscotch pudding 
1 C brown sugar 

Use a medium size Bundt pan, spray with cooking spray , layer rolls in pan 

In another pan 
Melt butter , pudding and brown sugar 
Just Mix-do not boil and then pour over the rolls.
COVER with plastic sprayed w/cooking spray. Let Rise, we set on counter overnight to rise then bake in the morning.

BAKE at 350 for 10-15 min then cover w/foil
And bake 10 more min until the bottom ones are done. 
Turn pan over on cookie sheet or a large platter to serve…the sauce will be spilling out.
ENJOY!! 😋
